name: Yolk (South Loop)
blog_description: Breakfast in Chicago is secretly run by Greek families. Yolk is everywhere. Meli Café is lights-out for hangovers. Lou Mitchell's near Union Station is a rite of passage.
general_description: Popular breakfast spot; big menu, reliable brunch.

name: Pequod's Pizza
blog_description: Deep dish: Pequod's, Lou Malnati's, Uno, Due. Tavern-style and more: Vito & Nick's, Pizzamici, Phil's, Bungalow by Middle Brow, Michael's, D'Agostino's, Gallucci, Spacca Napoli, Zaza's, Jimmy's Pizza Cafe.

name: Bavette's Bar & Boeuf
blog_description: Chicago is the steakhouse capital. Bavette's is A++, Chicago Cut has skyline views, Maple & Ash is a flex, Gibsons Italia does riverside decadence, RPM Steak is sleek, Gene & Georgetti is old-school, Boeufhaus is the chef's steakhouse, El Che is live-fire, Tango Sur is BYOB Argentine, Tre Dita is new-school.
general_description: Dark, jazzy, and perfect from top to bottom.
